  <section>
    <h1>Definition</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This page defines the canonical terms used across the website, diagrams, and patent materials.
      The definitions are system-agnostic, implementation-neutral, and problem-first.
    </p>

    <div class="doclinks">
      <a href="/boundaries.html">System boundaries &amp; non-goals</a>
      <a href="/#docs">Docs index</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="canonical-definition">
    <h2>Digital Action Receipt</h2>

    <div class="callout">
      <b>Digital Action Receipt</b> means an append-only, verifiable record generated by a <b>Receipt Service</b>
      <b>at the Moment of Action</b>, which records that a <b>Digital Action</b> occurred, together with
      <b>Integrity Information</b> sufficient for <b>Verification</b> of whether the receipt has been altered,
      <b>independent of later representation, explanation, or interpretation</b>.
    </div>

    <ul class="bullets">
      <li>Records occurrence (not correctness).</li>
      <li>Verifies integrity (not intent).</li>
      <li>Designed to be referenced later during disputes and “what happened?” questions.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="terms">
    <h2>Canonical terms</h2>

    <div class="grid">

      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Term</div>
        <b>Digital Action</b>
        <div class="kicker" style="margin-top:10px;">Definition</div>
        <div style="color:var(--muted); font-size:14px;">
          An action performed within a digital system by an actor (including a user, service, or agent),
          which produces an effect or state change that is meaningful to the system or its operators.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Term</div>
        <b>Moment of Action</b>
        <div class="kicker" style="margin-top:10px;">Definition</div>
        <div style="color:var(--muted); font-size:14px;">
          The time at which the Digital Action is performed or executed in the Action-Originating System,
          at which time a Digital Action Receipt is generated contemporaneously.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Term</div>
        <b>Receipt Service</b>
        <div class="kicker" style="margin-top:10px;">Definition</div>
        <div style="color:var(--muted); font-size:14px;">
          A system that generates a Digital Action Receipt upon invocation, and appends it to an
          Append-only Record Sequence. The Receipt Service does not explain, judge, or enforce actions.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Term</div>
        <b>Append-only</b>
        <div class="kicker" style="margin-top:10px;">Definition</div>
        <div style="color:var(--muted); font-size:14px;">
          A property of a record sequence in which new records may be added, while previously stored
          records are not modified or removed.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Term</div>
        <b>Append-only Record Sequence</b>
        <div class="kicker" style="margin-top:10px;">Definition</div>
        <div style="color:var(--muted); font-size:14px;">
          A sequence of stored Digital Action Receipts maintained in an append-only manner, such that
          receipts are added over time and prior receipts remain unchanged.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Term</div>
        <b>Integrity Information</b>
        <div class="kicker" style="margin-top:10px;">Definition</div>
        <div style="color:var(--muted); font-size:14px;">
          Information associated with a Digital Action Receipt that supports Verification of whether the
          receipt has been altered, without requiring privileged access to internal operational records.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Term</div>
        <b>Verification</b>
        <div class="kicker" style="margin-top:10px;">Definition</div>
        <div style="color:var(--muted); font-size:14px;">
          A process that confirms the integrity of a Digital Action Receipt by determining whether the
          receipt and its Integrity Information indicate alteration or mismatch. Verification does not
          validate correctness, intent, or justification.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Term</div>
        <b>Independent of representation/explanation</b>
        <div class="kicker" style="margin-top:10px;">Definition</div>
        <div style="color:var(--muted); font-size:14px;">
          A property indicating that the Digital Action Receipt is not dependent on later narratives,
          interpretations, reconstructions, or explanations of why an action occurred; it is evidence of
          occurrence generated at the Moment of Action.
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="what-it-proves">
    <h2>What a Digital Action Receipt proves (and does not prove)</h2>

    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Proves</div>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>A Digital Action occurred.</li>
          <li>The receipt was generated at the Moment of Action.</li>
          <li>The receipt’s integrity can be verified as unaltered (or flagged as mismatched).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="kicker">Does not prove</div>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>That the action was correct, permitted, or desirable.</li>
          <li>Why the action occurred, or what the actor intended.</li>
          <li>That a policy was followed, or that a decision was justified.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout" style="margin-top:12px;">
      <b>Verification is integrity-only.</b> No correctness • No intent • No enforcement.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="receipt-shape">
    <h2>Conceptual receipt contents (non-prescriptive)</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="font-size:14px;">
      A Digital Action Receipt may include a receipt identifier, a representation of the Moment of Action,
      and Integrity Information. This is an abstract example and not an implementation requirement.
    </p>

    <div class="code">
      <pre><code>{
  "receipt_id": "rct_…",
  "moment_of_action": "…",
  "action_summary": {
    "actor": "…",
    "action": "…",
    "object": "…",
    "ref": "…"
  },
  "integrity_information": {
    "…": "…"
  }
}</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="integration">
    <h2>How this integrates with existing systems</h2>
    <ul class="bullets">
      <li>The Action-Originating System performs a Digital Action.</li>
      <li>At the Moment of Action, the system invokes the Receipt Service (typically non-blocking).</li>
      <li>The Receipt Service generates a Digital Action Receipt and appends it to an Append-only Record Sequence.</li>
      <li>The receipt identifier is then referenced later (tickets, audits, reports, disputes) without requiring reconstruction.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

